  "title": "M&E Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Summary:</strong></u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We are seeking an experienced M&amp;E Coordinator to join our team. The candidate will be responsible for coordinating and managing the mechanical and electrical (M&amp;E) aspects of the project, ensuring timely and successful completion.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>1. Coordinate with M&amp;E consultants, contractors, and suppliers to ensure compliance with project specifications and requirements.</p>\n<p>2. Review and comment on M&amp;E shop drawings, method statements, and material submissions.</p>\n<p>3. Conduct site inspections to monitor M&amp;E installation works and ensure compliance with project requirements.</p>\n<p>4. Identify and resolve M&amp;E-related issues and defects.</p>\n<p>5. Coordinate with other project teams (e.g., architectural, structural) to ensure integration and compatibility of M&amp;E systems.</p>\n<p>6. Develop and maintain M&amp;E-related project documentation, including records of inspections, testing, and commissioning.</p>\n<p>7. Ensure compliance with relevant building codes, regulations, and industry standards.</p>\n<p>8. Collaborate with the project team to develop and implement project schedules, budgets, and resource allocation plans.</p>\n<p>9. Provide technical support and guidance to site staff and contractors.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p>\n<ol>\n  <li>Relevant experience on construction industry for new build and A&amp;A work for condo, factory. relevant certificates recognise by local authorities eg BCA, MOM</li>\n  <li>Fresh candidate will be guided along the way</li>\n</ol>",
